Enable Sharing Inheritance
Use sharing inheritance to let CRM Analytics apply the same sharing setup for your datasets as Salesforce uses for your objects. Sharing inheritance increases access accuracy and reduces the need for complicated security predicates for most objects and situations.

As an admin for your Salesforce org, you likely use a combination of sharing settings to provide users access to Salesforce data appropriate to their roles. For supported objects, you can enable sharing inheritance in CRM Analytics to use the Salesforce sharing settings in CRM Analytics.

Enable Sharing Inheritance
Turn on sharing inheritance and select the objects to use as a sharing source. Determine If Sharing Inheritance Will Work for You
Review these supported objects, maximum number of sharing descriptors, and considerations. Set Sharing Inheritance for a Data Prep Recipe
Specify the sharing inheritance settings when generating a dataset from a Data Prep recipe, then set a default security predicate.
